           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-2">Another <supplied reason="subaudible">Tai</supplied> Kandeṅ. Total: 9 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 5 animal keepers <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 16 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>, 2 slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>lap</foreign></supplied>; grand total: 32.</p>
              <p n="3-13">Sruk Devālaya: Si Kanloñ, Gho KandiL Gho Kan-in, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Chpoṅ, Gho Paṇdan, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kanpon, Gvāl <gap reason="lost"/>, Gvāl Dharmma, Gvāl Khmau, Gvāl Saṁ-ap, Gvāl Kañjā, Gvāl Kaṁpañ, Gvāl Vramoy, Gvāl Adit, Gvāl Amr̥ta, Gvāl Kanden, Gvāl Thkāṁ, Tai Phle, Tai Panlas, Tai Svāy, Tai Kantvan, another Tai Kantvan, Tai Paṁnaṅ, Tai Kaṁvraḥ, Tai Kaṁprvat. Total: 8 male slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gho</foreign></supplied>, 11 animal slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>gvāl</foreign></supplied>, 8 female slaves <supplied reason="explanation"><foreign>tai</foreign></supplied>; grand total: 27.</p>
              <p n="13-20">The people from village of Āśra: Gho Kaṁvai, Gho Hari, Gho Kan-as, Gho Kanteṅ, Gho Prāṇa, Gho Kaṁvit, Gho Nirantaraśiva, Gho Khñuṁ, Gho La-au, Gho Kanrau, Gho śri, Gho Ratnamaya, Gho Iśānaśiva, Gvāl Camval, Gvāl Rāja, Gvāl Kaṁpit, Gvāl Kanteṅ, Gvāl Khmau, Tai Kañji<gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Vraḥ <gap reason="lost"/>, Tai Kaṁvrau. Total: 21.</p>
              <p n="21-26">Sruk <gap reason="lost"/>: Si Śrimahendra, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Thkap, Gho Krau, Gho Kaṁvrau, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>, Gho Kañcaṅ, Gho Kan-a, Gho <gap reason="lost"/>deha, another Gho Kan-ā, Gho Adit, Gho Iśānavyāpi, Gho Kañcañ, Gho Vahanadhi, Gho Khñuṁ, Gho pravā<gap reason="lost"/></p>
